  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "M&E Engineer",
  "description": "<p>Job Description &amp; Requirements</p>\n<p>The MEP Engineer is responsible for all aspects of mechanical and electrical engineering activities, processes, and construction of projects.</p>\n<p>· Monitor and report on the progress of work to project manager;</p>\n<p>· Control the progress of RFA, RFI, Shop Drawings, Technical Submissions and Equipment/Material Procurement/Fabrication/Delivery Status for on-time completion.</p>\n<p>· Coordinate with client’s representatives, consultants, and subcontractors on all technical matters, including submission of method statement, drawings, materials, samples and work progress;</p>\n<p>· Control site progress &amp; installation quality as per approved Shop Drawings, Technical Submissions and Equipment/Material Procurement/Fabrication/Delivery Schedule for on-time completion.</p>\n<p>· Carry out inspection of MEP works prior to concreting or subsequent construction works;</p>\n<p>· Assist in supervising and coordinating MEP services work closely with other departments;</p>\n<p>· Assist for submission of evaluation of progress claim, variation work to M&amp;E Manager</p>\n<p>· Participate in all relevant project review meetings, site meetings, design meetings, and other project relevant meetings;</p>\n<p>· Responsible for carrying out M&amp;E technical meetings and resolving technical issues with record.</p>\n<p>· Responsible for M&amp;E drawing coordination and production of CSD and individual service drawings quality.</p>\n<p>· Responsible for conducting QA/QC inspection, managing RE, RTO and responsible for clearing QA/QC inspections to meet with construction schedule.</p>\n<p>· Provide and maintain all site inspection records &amp; T&amp;C records up to date.</p>\n<p>· Ensure quality of MEP workmanship and compliance with safety and environmental requirements</p>\n<p>· Provide and maintain all site inspection records &amp; T&amp;C records up to date.</p>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<p>· Diploma or Degree in Electrical/Mechanical Engineering, recognized by PE Board Singapore;</p>\n<p>· Minimum 5 years’ work experience related projects in Singapore building and construction industry;</p>\n<p>· Electrical/Mechanical Engineering experience in HDB projects or high-rise developments is a must;</p>\n<p>· Possess strong Electrical/Mechanical knowledge with hands-on experiences;</p>\n<p>· Strong communication skills with the ability to coordinate with site teams to execute work</p>",
